---
import DocsLayout from "../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";

const TITLE = "Overview";
const DESCRIPTION = "MeasureKit — Unit-aware physics computation for Python. Zero runtime dependencies, optional Rust core, multi-backend tensors.";
---

<DocsLayout title={TITLE} description={DESCRIPTION} activeSection="overview">
  <!-- Hero -->
  <div class="hero">
    <div class="hero-badge">
      <span class="badge badge-green">Beta</span>
      <span>v0.1.8 · MIT License · Python 3.10+</span>
    </div>
    <img src="/logo.jpg" alt="MeasureKit logo" width="100" height="100" class="hero-logo" />
    <h1>MeasureKit</h1>
    <p class="hero-lead">
      Unit-aware physics computation for Python. Attach physical units to numbers, 
      NumPy arrays, PyTorch tensors, and JAX arrays — and let the engine keep you honest.
    </p>
    <div class="hero-install">
      <div class="install-cmd">
        <span class="prompt">$</span>
        <code>pip install measurekit</code>
        <button class="copy-btn-hero" data-copy="pip install measurekit" title="Copy">
          <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="9" y="9" width="13" height="13" rx="2" ry="2"></rect><path d="M5 15H4a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h9a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v1"></path></svg>
        </button>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-links">
      <a href="/quickstart" class="btn-primary">Get Started →</a>
      <a href="/install" class="btn-secondary">Installation Options</a>
      <a href="https://github.com/Alexisrx96/measurekit" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-ghost">GitHub</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Quick Demo -->
  <section class="demo-section">
    <h2>See it in action</h2>
    <div class="demo-grid">
      <div class="demo-card">
        <div class="demo-label">Python API</div>
        <pre><code><span class="kw">from</span> measurekit <span class="kw">import</span> Q_

<span class="cm"># Unit-safe arithmetic</span>
d = Q_(10, <span class="str">"km"</span>)
t = Q_(2, <span class="str">"hr"</span>)
v = d / t

<span class="fn">print</span>(v.to(<span class="str">"m/s"</span>))  <span class="cm"># 1.3888... m/s</span>
d + t            <span class="cm"># ❌ raises: length + time</span></code></pre>
      </div>
      <div class="demo-card">
        <div class="demo-label">Grammar / REPL</div>
        <pre><code><span class="cm"># Notation like on paper</span>
force = 500 N
area  = 2 m^2
stress = force / area

stress =&gt; kPa      <span class="cm"># 0.25 kPa</span>
stress == 250 Pa   <span class="cm"># True</span></code></pre>
      </div>
      <div class="demo-card">
        <div class="demo-label">Uncertainty Propagation</div>
        <pre><code><span class="kw">from</span> measurekit <span class="kw">import</span> Q_

g = Q_(9.81, <span class="str">"m/s^2"</span>, uncertainty=0.02)
m = Q_(5.0,  <span class="str">"kg"</span>,    uncertainty=0.1)

F = g * m
<span class="cm"># F = 49.05 ± 0.99 N</span></code></pre>
      </div>
      <div class="demo-card">
        <div class="demo-label">Terminal Calculator</div>
        <pre><code><span class="prompt">$</span> python -m measurekit <span class="str">"500 N / 2 m^2 =&gt; kPa"</span>
0.25 kPa

<span class="prompt">$</span> python -m measurekit
<span class="prompt">mk&gt;</span> g = 9.81 +/- 0.02 m/s^2
<span class="prompt">mk&gt;</span> g =&gt; ft/s^2
32.185... ft/s^2</code></pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What is MeasureKit -->
  <section>
    <h2>What is MeasureKit?</h2>
    <p>
      MeasureKit started as "The Over-Engineered Homework Validator" — one developer wanted to 
      check physics exercises and instead built a <strong>backend-agnostic, JIT-compilable 
      dimension engine</strong>. It applies enterprise architecture patterns to unit handling, 
      giving you safety and expressiveness usually reserved for research frameworks.
    </p>
    <p>
      Unlike Pint (which is excellent and battle-tested), MeasureKit focuses specifically on:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>JIT-compiled unit safety on <strong>PyTorch and JAX tensors</strong></li>
      <li><strong>Correlated uncertainty propagation</strong> with a full covariance store</li>
      <li><strong>Zero-dependency base install</strong> — just Python 3.10+</li>
      <li>A <strong>natural-language grammar</strong> for writing physics like on paper</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- Features Grid -->
  <section>
    <h2>Features</h2>
    <div class="card-grid">
      <div class="card feat-card">
        <div class="feat-icon">📐</div>
        <h3>Dimensional Analysis</h3>
        <p>Automatic unit tracking through all arithmetic. Illegal operations (meters + seconds) raise clear errors.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card feat-card">
        <div class="feat-icon">🔢</div>
        <h3>Multi-Backend Tensors</h3>
        <p>NumPy, PyTorch, and JAX backends selected automatically from the value you pass in.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card feat-card">
        <div class="feat-icon">📊</div>
        <h3>Uncertainty Propagation</h3>
        <p>Independent and correlated error propagation. A covariance store tracks correlations so x − x = 0 exactly.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card feat-card">
        <div class="feat-icon">⚡</div>
        <h3>JIT Compilation</h3>
        <p>Unit checks at trace time, raw tensors at runtime. Under 1.1× overhead vs pure PyTorch with torch.compile.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card feat-card">
        <div class="feat-icon">🦀</div>
        <h3>Optional Rust Core</h3>
        <p>measurekit-core (via PyO3) accelerates unit algebra. Every path has a pure-Python fallback.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card feat-card">
        <div class="feat-icon">✍️</div>
        <h3>Grammar & REPL</h3>
        <p>Write <code>force = 500 N</code> in Python, files, or interactively — like GNU units with error propagation.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card feat-card">
        <div class="feat-icon">🔍</div>
        <h3>Static Typing</h3>
        <p>mypy plugin narrows <code>Q_(v, "m/s")</code> to unit-aware literal types. Pandas and Pydantic integrations included.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card feat-card">
        <div class="feat-icon">📚</div>
        <h3>125+ Units & 400+ Constants</h3>
        <p>28 dimensions, 24 SI prefixes, and 400+ CODATA 2022 physical constants built in.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Stats -->
  <section>
    <h2>By the numbers</h2>
    <div class="stats-grid">
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="stat-big">0</div>
        <div class="stat-desc">runtime dependencies (base install)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="stat-big">125+</div>
        <div class="stat-desc">units across 28 dimensions</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="stat-big">400+</div>
        <div class="stat-desc">CODATA 2022 physical constants</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="stat-big">&lt;1.1×</div>
        <div class="stat-desc">overhead vs raw PyTorch (compiled)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="stat-big">80%+</div>
        <div class="stat-desc">test coverage (CI-gated)</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="stat-big">3.10–3.14</div>
        <div class="stat-desc">Python versions supported</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Honest Performance -->
  <section>
    <h2>Honest performance</h2>
    <p>Most libraries claim "zero overhead". Here's what that actually means in MeasureKit:</p>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Mode</th>
          <th>Speed</th>
          <th>Notes</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Eager (plain Python)</strong></td>
          <td><span class="badge badge-yellow">10–100× slower</span></td>
          <td>Python object allocation + unit validation. Fine for data checking, not hot loops.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Compiled (torch.compile / jax.jit)</strong></td>
          <td><span class="badge badge-green">&lt;1.1× overhead</span></td>
          <td>Units validate at trace time, stripped from compiled graph. The real "zero overhead".</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>With Rust core</strong></td>
          <td><span class="badge badge-blue">Eager speedup</span></td>
          <td>Helps with scalar eager mode. Crossing the Python–Rust boundary still has cost.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>First import</strong></td>
          <td>~0.5 s</td>
          <td>Tracked budget in CI. Does not include torch/scipy startup.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="cta-section">
    <h2>Ready to start?</h2>
    <p>Head to the Quick Start guide to have MeasureKit running in under 5 minutes.</p>
    <div class="cta-actions">
      <a href="/quickstart" class="btn-primary">Quick Start Guide →</a>
      <a href="/install" class="btn-secondary">Installation options</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>

<style>
  /* Hero */
  .hero {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 2rem 0 3rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .hero-badge {
    display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; gap: 0.5rem;
    color: var(--text3); font-size: 0.8rem; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }
  .hero-logo {
    border-radius: 16px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border2);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    display: block;
    margin-inline: auto;
  }
  .hero h1 {
    font-size: 2.75rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #e2e8f0, #a5b4fc);
    -webkit-background-clip: text; -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
    border: none;
  }
  .hero-lead {
    font-size: 1.1rem; max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto 1.75rem;
    color: var(--text2);
  }
  .hero-install { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .install-cmd {
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem;
    background: var(--panel); border: 1px solid var(--border2);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: 0.75rem 1.25rem;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 1rem;
  }
  .prompt { color: var(--text3); }
  .install-cmd code { color: var(--accent2); }
  .copy-btn-hero {
    background: none; border: none; cursor: pointer; color: var(--text3);
    transition: color 0.2s; display: flex; align-items: center;
  }
  .copy-btn-hero:hover { color: var(--text); }
  .hero-links { display: flex; gap: 0.75rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }

  .btn-primary {
    background: var(--accent); color: white;
    padding: 0.6rem 1.4rem; border-radius: var(--radius);
    font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.9rem;
    transition: background 0.2s, transform 0.1s;
    display: inline-block;
  }
  .btn-primary:hover { background: var(--accent2); transform: translateY(-1px); text-decoration: none; }
  .btn-secondary {
    background: var(--panel); color: var(--text);
    border: 1px solid var(--border2);
    padding: 0.6rem 1.4rem; border-radius: var(--radius);
    font-weight: 500; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.9rem;
    transition: border-color 0.2s; display: inline-block;
  }
  .btn-secondary:hover { border-color: var(--accent); text-decoration: none; }
  .btn-ghost {
    color: var(--text2); padding: 0.6rem 1.4rem;
    border-radius: var(--radius); font-size: 0.9rem;
    text-decoration: none; transition: color 0.2s;
    display: inline-block;
  }
  .btn-ghost:hover { color: var(--text); text-decoration: none; }

  /* Demo */
  .demo-section h2 { margin-top: 0; }
  .demo-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem; margin: 1rem 0;
  }
  .demo-card {
    background: var(--panel); border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg); overflow: hidden;
  }
  .demo-label {
    background: var(--panel2); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 0.5rem 1rem; font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text3); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  }
  .demo-card pre {
    margin: 0; border: none; border-radius: 0;
    background: transparent; padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
  }
  .kw { color: #c792ea; }
  .str { color: #c3e88d; }
  .cm { color: #546e7a; font-style: italic; }
  .fn { color: #82aaff; }
  .prompt { color: var(--text3); }

  /* Features */
  .feat-card h3 { margin-top: 0.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.35rem; font-size: 1rem; }
  .feat-card p { margin: 0; font-size: 0.875rem; }
  .feat-icon { font-size: 1.5rem; }

  /* Stats */
  .stats-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(150px, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem; margin: 1rem 0;
  }
  .stat-card {
    background: var(--panel); border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: 1.25rem;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .stat-big {
    font-size: 1.75rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--accent2);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }
  .stat-desc { font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--text3); }

  /* CTA */
  .cta-section {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(99,102,241,0.08), rgba(129,140,248,0.04));
    border: 1px solid rgba(99,102,241,0.2);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: 2rem;
    text-align: center; margin-top: 3rem;
  }
  .cta-section h2 { border: none; margin-top: 0; }
  .cta-actions { display: flex; gap: 0.75rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-top: 1rem; }
</style>

<script>
  document.querySelectorAll('.copy-btn-hero').forEach(btn => {
    btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
      const text = btn.getAttribute('data-copy') || '';
      navigator.clipboard.writeText(text).then(() => {
        const original = btn.innerHTML;
        btn.innerHTML = '✓';
        setTimeout(() => { btn.innerHTML = original; }, 2000);
      });
    });
  });
</script>
